      • treeMap

        public static final <K extends Comparable<?>,V> java.util.Map<K,V> treeMap()
        Unsynchronized map for per-thread/local shortlife processing. This map doesn't guarantee concurrent write access, but it is optimized for fast creation. Implementation may loose some read/write speed on large amounts of data in order to make best effort of fast creation. So it happens to be just nice little macro for new TreeMap() constructor which takes care about supplying automatic template types.
